# Architettura Utenti: Members, Sub-Members, Customers e Admin

## Panoramica

Il progetto ha una struttura multi-account con quattro tipi di utenti:
- **Admin**: amministratore del sistema, vede tutto (bypass account isolation)
- **Members (Owner)**: utenti che acquistano il servizio con piani di licenza, proprietari dell'account
- **Sub-Members**: membri con permessi limitati, dipendenti/dipendenti del Member Owner
- **Customers**: utenti dei Members con accesso limitato alla piattaforma

## Architettura Database

### Tabella `users` (Autenticazione Base)
Tutti gli utenti (Admin, Members, Sub-Members, Customers) hanno un record in questa tabella per l'autenticazione.

**Campi base Laravel**:
- `id` (bigint, primary key)
- `email` (string, unique)
- `email_verified_at` (timestamp, nullable)
- `password` (string)
- `remember_token` (string, nullable)
- `created_at` (timestamp)
- `updated_at` (timestamp)
- `deleted_at` (timestamp, nullable) - Soft Delete

**Campi aggiuntivi**:
- `user_type` (string, enum: 'admin', 'member', 'sub_member', 'customer') - tipo di utente
- `is_active` (boolean, default: true) - stato attivo/disattivo

### Tabella `members`
Rappresenta sia i membri proprietari dell'account che i sub-members con permessi limitati.

**Relazioni**:
- `user_id` (bigint, foreign key → users.id, unique) - relazione 1:1 con users
- `license_plan_id` (bigint, foreign key → license_plans.id) - piano di licenza (solo per owner)
- `parent_member_id` (bigint, foreign key → members.id, nullable) - se non NULL, è un sub-member

**Campi specifici**:
- `id` (bigint, primary key)
- `user_id` (bigint, unique, foreign key)
- `parent_member_id` (bigint, foreign key, nullable) - **IMPORTANTE**: 
  - NULL = Member Owner (proprietario dell'account)
  - NOT NULL = Sub-Member (dipendente/dipendente del Member Owner)
- `license_plan_id` (bigint, foreign key, nullable) - solo per owner, NULL per sub-members
- `is_owner` (boolean, default: false) - flag per identificare rapidamente se è owner
- `company_name` (string, nullable) - solo per owner
- `company_vat` (string, nullable) - solo per owner
- `first_name` (string, nullable) - per sub-members
- `last_name` (string, nullable) - per sub-members
- `subscription_started_at` (timestamp, nullable) - solo per owner
- `subscription_ends_at` (timestamp, nullable) - solo per owner
- `trial_ends_at` (timestamp, nullable) - solo per owner
- `is_trial` (boolean, default: false) - solo per owner
- `max_customers` (integer, nullable) - limite customers in base al piano (solo per owner)
- `max_sub_members` (integer, nullable) - limite sub-members in base al piano (solo per owner)
- `settings` (json, nullable) - configurazioni personalizzate del membro
- `permissions` (json, nullable) - permessi specifici per sub-members (override dei permessi di base)
- `stripe_customer_id` (string, nullable) - ID cliente Stripe
- `stripe_subscription_id` (string, nullable) - ID subscription Stripe
- `subscription_status` (string, nullable) - stato subscription (active, trial, cancelled, past_due)
- `created_at` (timestamp)
- `updated_at` (timestamp)
- `deleted_at` (timestamp, nullable) - Soft Delete

**Note**:
- Se `parent_member_id` è NULL e `is_owner = true` → Member Owner
- Se `parent_member_id` è NOT NULL e `is_owner = false` → Sub-Member
- I Sub-Members condividono lo stesso account del Member Owner (`parent_member_id`)

### Tabella `accounts`
Rappresenta gli utenti che accedono al pannello di amministrazione (Admin e altri ruoli amministrativi).

**Relazioni**:
- `user_id` (bigint, foreign key → users.id, unique) - relazione 1:1 con users

**Campi specifici**:
- `id` (bigint, primary key)
- `user_id` (bigint, unique, foreign key)
- `first_name` (string, nullable)
- `last_name` (string, nullable)
- `department` (string, nullable) - dipartimento/ufficio
- `role_level` (string, nullable) - livello di accesso (es: 'super_admin', 'admin', 'moderator')
- `notes` (text, nullable) - note aggiuntive
- `last_login_at` (timestamp, nullable) - ultimo accesso
- `settings` (json, nullable) - configurazioni personalizzate dell'account
- `created_at` (timestamp)
- `updated_at` (timestamp)
- `deleted_at` (timestamp, nullable) - Soft Delete

**Note**:
- Gli Admin hanno un record in questa tabella per gestire informazioni aggiuntive
- Non hanno account isolation (vedono tutto)
- Possono avere diversi `role_level` per gestire livelli di accesso amministrativo

### Tabella `customers`
Rappresenta i clienti dei Members (Owner) con accesso limitato.

**Relazioni**:
- `user_id` (bigint, foreign key → users.id, unique) - relazione 1:1 con users
- `member_id` (bigint, foreign key → members.id) - Member Owner proprietario (account)
  - **IMPORTANTE**: Si riferisce sempre al Member Owner (`is_owner = true`), non ai Sub-Members

**Campi specifici**:
- `id` (bigint, primary key)
- `user_id` (bigint, unique, foreign key)
- `member_id` (bigint, foreign key) - **IMPORTANTE**: identifica il account
- `first_name` (string)
- `last_name` (string)
- `phone` (string, nullable)
- `address` (text, nullable)
- `custom_fields` (json, nullable) - campi personalizzabili per customer
- `created_at` (timestamp)
- `updated_at` (timestamp)
- `deleted_at` (timestamp, nullable) - Soft Delete

### Tabella `custom_permissions`
Gestisce permessi custom per **Account** (admin) e **Sub-Members** (Member).

**Relazioni**:
- `permissionable_type` + `permissionable_id` (polymorphic: `Account` | `Member`)
- `granted_by` (foreign key → users.id, nullable) - chi ha concesso il permesso

**Campi specifici**:
- `id` (bigint, primary key)
- `permissionable_type` (string) - tipo: `App\Models\Account` o `App\Models\Member`
- `permissionable_id` (bigint) - ID dell'Account o Member
- `domain` (string) - dominio del permesso (es: 'cargo_provider', 'dashboard')
- `permission` (string) - permesso specifico (es: 'index', 'create', 'update', 'delete')
- `granted` (boolean, default: true) - true = concesso, false = negato esplicitamente
- `granted_by` (bigint, foreign key, nullable) - ID utente che ha concesso il permesso
- `notes` (text, nullable) - note sul permesso
- `expires_at` (timestamp, nullable) - scadenza permesso (opzionale, per permessi temporanei)
- `created_at` (timestamp)
- `updated_at` (timestamp)
- `deleted_at` (timestamp, nullable) - Soft Delete

**Indici**:
- `(permissionable_type, permissionable_id, domain, permission)` - unique
- `(permissionable_type, permissionable_id)` - query per utente
- `(domain, permission)` - query per dominio
- `(granted_by)` - query per chi ha concesso
- `(expires_at)` - query per permessi in scadenza
- `(deleted_at)` - soft delete

**Note**:
- Permessi custom hanno **priorità** su Spatie Permission
- Permessi custom hanno **priorità** su JSON permissions (backward compatibility per Sub-Members)
- Admin: se ha custom permission → usa quello, altrimenti bypass completo (vede tutto)
- Sub-Members: custom permission > JSON permission > default (false)

### Tabella `license_plans`
Piani di licenza per i Members.

**Campi**:
- `id` (bigint, primary key)
- `name` (string) - es: "Free", "Basic", "Professional", "Enterprise"
- `slug` (string, unique)
- `description` (text, nullable)
- `price` (decimal, nullable)
- `billing_period` (string, nullable) - monthly, yearly
- `trial_days` (integer, default: 0) - giorni di trial
- `max_customers` (integer, nullable) - NULL = illimitato
- `max_sub_members` (integer, nullable) - NULL = illimitato
- `features` (json, nullable) - feature del piano
- `is_active` (boolean, default: true)
- `sort_order` (integer, default: 0)
- `created_at` (timestamp)
- `updated_at` (timestamp)
- `deleted_at` (timestamp, nullable)

## Architettura Models

### User Model
```php
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\HasOne;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\SoftDeletes;
use Spatie\Permission\Traits\HasRoles;

class User extends Authenticatable
{
    use SoftDeletes, HasRoles;

    protected $fillable = [
        'email',
        'password',
        'user_type',
        'is_active',
    ];

    protected $casts = [
        'is_active' => 'boolean',
        'email_verified_at' => 'datetime',
    ];

    // Relazioni
    public function member(): HasOne
    {
        return $this->hasOne(Member::class);
    }

    public function customer(): HasOne
    {
        return $this->hasOne(Customer::class);
    }

    public function account(): HasOne
    {
        return $this->hasOne(Account::class);
    }

    // Helper methods
    public function isMember(): bool
    {
        return in_array($this->user_type, ['member', 'sub_member']);
    }

    public function isMemberOwner(): bool
    {
        return $this->user_type === 'member' && $this->member && $this->member->is_owner;
    }

    public function isSubMember(): bool
    {
        return $this->user_type === 'sub_member' || ($this->member && !$this->member->is_owner);
    }

    public function isCustomer(): bool
    {
        return $this->user_type === 'customer';
    }

    public function isAdmin(): bool
    {
        return $this->hasRole('admin');
    }

    // Accessor per ottenere il profilo completo
    public function profile()
    {
        if ($this->isAdmin()) {
            return $this->account;
        }
        
        if ($this->isCustomer()) {
            return $this->customer;
        }
        
        return $this->member;
    }

    // Ottenere il Member Owner dell'account corrente
    public function getOwnerMember(): ?Member
    {
        // Admin non ha account, vede tutto
        if ($this->isAdmin()) {
            return null;
        }

        if ($this->isMemberOwner()) {
            return $this->member;
        }

        if ($this->isSubMember() && $this->member) {
            return $this->member->ownerMember;
        }

        if ($this->isCustomer() && $this->customer) {
            return $this->customer->member;
        }

        return null;
    }
}
```

### Member Model
```php
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\BelongsTo;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\HasMany;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\SoftDeletes;
use Spatie\Activitylog\Traits\LogsActivity;
use Spatie\Activitylog\LogOptions;

class Member extends Model
{
    use SoftDeletes, LogsActivity;

    protected $fillable = [
        'user_id',
        'parent_member_id',
        'license_plan_id',
        'is_owner',
        'company_name',
        'company_vat',
        'first_name',
        'last_name',
        'subscription_started_at',
        'subscription_ends_at',
        'trial_ends_at',
        'is_trial',
        'max_customers',
        'max_sub_members',
        'settings',
        'permissions',
        'stripe_customer_id',
        'stripe_subscription_id',
        'subscription_status',
    ];

    protected $casts = [
        'is_owner' => 'boolean',
        'is_trial' => 'boolean',
        'subscription_started_at' => 'datetime',
        'subscription_ends_at' => 'datetime',
        'trial_ends_at' => 'datetime',
        'settings' => 'array',
        'permissions' => 'array',
    ];

    // Relazioni
    public function user(): BelongsTo
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(User::class);
    }

    public function licensePlan(): BelongsTo
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(LicensePlan::class);
    }

    public function ownerMember(): BelongsTo
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(Member::class, 'parent_member_id');
    }

    public function subMembers(): HasMany
    {
        return $this->hasMany(Member::class, 'parent_member_id');
    }

    public function customers(): HasMany
    {
        return $this->hasMany(Customer::class);
    }

    // Helper methods
    public function isOwner(): bool
    {
        return $this->is_owner === true && $this->parent_member_id === null;
    }

    public function isSubMember(): bool
    {
        return $this->is_owner === false && $this->parent_member_id !== null;
    }

    // Ottenere il Member Owner (se stesso se è owner, altrimenti il parent)
    public function getOwner(): Member
    {
        return $this->isOwner() ? $this : $this->ownerMember;
    }

    // Verifica permessi per Sub-Members
    public function canAccessDomain(string $domain, string $permission): bool
    {
        if ($this->isOwner()) {
            return true; // Owner ha sempre accesso completo
        }

        if ($this->isSubMember()) {
            $permissions = $this->permissions ?? [];
            return $permissions['domains'][$domain][$permission] ?? false;
        }

        return false;
    }

    // Activity Log
    public function getActivitylogOptions(): LogOptions
    {
        return LogOptions::defaults()
            ->logOnly([
                'company_name',
                'first_name',
                'last_name',
                'license_plan_id',
                'parent_member_id',
                'max_customers',
                'max_sub_members',
                'permissions',
                'subscription_status',
                'is_trial',
            ])
            ->logOnlyDirty()
            ->dontSubmitEmptyLogs();
    }
}
```

